Several armed robbers on Monday afternoon invaded and raided a commercial bank in Idoani in Ose Local Government Area, Ondo State, Southwest Nigeria.
The bank, which is located at Isewa quarters, is the only financial institution in the community. It was gathered that the robbers are carried out the operations with impunity and without any modicum of resistance or intervention.
They were said to have gained entry into the bank after blowing up the entrance door with explosive dynamite.
The extent of damage or amount of money stolen was not ascertained at the time of this report. However, National Daily will monitor the trend to bring you update.

			
